post_text: The first 7 days of school this year our students learned all about the 7 Habits and how they can transform their life and our school and classroom culture. One of the most powerful pieces of our leadership curriculum is teaching the students to focus on the things in which they have control over and not focus on the things they have little to no control over. Watch this video to learn about the power of the circle of influence: https://youtu.be/uj8dmSgQa1c

post_text: We are continuing to work with state and local health and business leaders as well as GWA parents and staff to come up with the safest and most appropriate way to open this fall. post_text:
The hiring committee has selected Mr. Chance Manzanares as a new Assistant Director effective May 26, 2020. Please read this short introduction:

After graduating from Southern Utah University I began my education career teaching 6th grade and more recently 4th grade here at GWA. During my time in the classroom I gained a passion for witnessing my students grow and develop both academically and socially. I loved seeing my students become resilient, push through challenges, and transition into school leaders.

As GWA's new Assistant Director I plan on extending my influence outside of the classroom. I am dedicated to ensuring that our students are learning at high levels and are recieving the support they need in order to be successful. I will help create a postive environment that promotes collaboration, understanding, and learning.

I have a strong desire and passion to empower both our amazing students and our exceptional teachers and staff. I am grateful for this opportunity and am appreciative of the tremendous support.

post_text:
Habit #5: Seek First to Understand Then to Be Understood
Honesty!
Seeking to be understood involves trust. One way to build trust with others is to be honest. Honesty is the gateway to effective communication.
text:
Habit #5: Seek First to Understand Then to Be Understood
Honesty!
Seeking to be understood involves trust. One way to build trust with others is to be honest. Honesty is the gateway to effective communication.

post_text:
Habit 5 emphasizes the importance of good communication. Good communication starts with truly understanding each other. Some effective practices are:
Listen with the intent to understand
Ask clarifying questions
Respect, mutual understanding, empathy, and courage are character traits of someone who is working on this habit.

KINDERGARTEN TEACHER ASSISTANT (PART TIME 29 HOURS PER WEEK MON-FRI)
George Washington Academy is currently looking to hire a Part Time Kindergarten Teacher Assistant for a maximum of 29 hours per week Monday-Friday. As a Teacher Assistant you will perform duties that are instructional in nature or deliver services to students. You will serve in a position for which a teacher or another professional has ultimate responsibility for the design and implementation of educational services. Bachelor’s Degree is preferred and experience working with children is a plus, but not required. Compensation is $10.82 per hour. If you are interested in working at GWA, applications are available on our website: http://www.gwacademy.org. All employees are required to pass a BCI Background check at their own expense.

post_text:
LUNCHROOM AIDES (PART TIME 18 HOURS PER WEEK)

George Washington Academy is currently looking to hire lunchroom aides to assist with student supervision during lunch, recess, and general maintenance. You will need to have physical strength (carry bulky objects of up to 50 pounds with or without assistance), and the agility to pull, push, squat, twist, turn and lift. This includes both inside and outside responsibilities. Pay is $10.82 per hour for a total of 18 hours per week 10:30 am – 2:00 pm Monday - Friday. All employees are required to pass a BCI background check at their own expense. Must submit an application to be considered for an interview. Applications are available on our website at http://www.gwacademy.org. Please send resume and application to hr@gwacademy.org

Our GWA STEM EXPO is tonight from 6:00-8:00 pm at GWA. This will be an event you will not want to miss. The STEM EXPO will have a planetarium, virtual reality areas, animal encounters, LEGO-ify using Adobe, coding, chemistry shows, art demonstrations and much more. Many of these demonstrations have limited availability and there will only be a certain number of shows for each event. Tickets will be handed out at check-in for the events. This is a free event and all are welcome.

shared_text:
City of St. George
February 28, 2019 at 7:26 PM ·

The good news: It's going to be a little easier to make that left at the intersection of 3000 East and 2000 South.

The other news: Those traveling north and south only on 3000 East can expect a slightly longer commute.

This is a 4-way stop sign, effective as of this morning. The stop sign is temporary; it's the same intersection where a stoplight is scheduled to begin construction Monday. We will also have stoplights soon at both 1450 South and 2450 South along 3000 East.

Stay safe!

post_text:
PART TIME SPECIAL EDUCATION TEACHER (29 hours per week)
George Washington Academy is looking to hire a part time SPED Teacher who has experience working with students who have mild-moderate and profound disabilities. Is knowledgeable and confident in planning, writing, and implementing IEPs and processes a keen understanding of the special needs and different styles of students with disabilities. Join our team and work for a school with high standards and an exceptional track record for providing high quality education! Applicants should have a current Utah credential for K-8 and a desire to provide a high quality, academically rigorous educational experience to students. Applicants should also be aware of our school's mission and philosophy and have a basic knowledge of the curriculums we use to support our high academics. Competitive Salary. Applicants will not be considered without cover letter, application, and letters of recommendation. Applications are available on our website: http://www.gwacademy.org Please send resume and application to hr@gwacademy.org.

Please come to our wrap-up meeting on Wednesday, October 24th, after drop off. This is a great time to discuss any suggestions or notes you have about your volunteer time or ideas to help make the carnival better. Thank you to everyone who contributed or volunteered! Your efforts made the carnival a success, which directly benefits all of our students. If you are unable to come to the meeting but still have suggestions, please email Suzanne at fallcarnival@gwacademy.org. Thank you again, GWA parents are the best!

post_text:
More Money Drive news! Thank you to all that donated to this year's Money Drive! The total amount raised was $20,926.95! We will have a school-wide Free-Dress Day next Wednesday, October 10th for meeting our goal.

The team that raised the most money and winner of the "Fandom T-Shirt" Day is the Red Team (Teachers: Woodcock, Cooke, McArthur, Larkin, Lamb, Townes). The students on this team will have their reward day this Friday, October 5th. Students will be able to wear their favorite "fan" shirt with uniform bottoms and shoes. Examples of "Fandom T-Shirts" are Harry Potter, unicorns, BYU, sports team, dinosaurs, Star Wars, GWA, or anything you are a fan of.

The winner of the class competition and Ice Cream Party is Ms. Lamb's 4th-grade class! They will choose a later date to celebrate this.

Individual prizes will be handed out later today!

Preferred Substitute Teacher
George Washington Academy is currently looking to hire a high quality preferred substitute teacher. Substitute teaching is for grades K-8 and may also cover for other positions. Bachelor's Degree preferred and experience working with children is a plus. If you are interested in substituting at GWA, applications are available below. All substitutes are required to pass a BCI Background check at their own expense and go through GWA substitute training. Please send resume and application to hr@gwacademy.org

So far we have collected $9,830 for the PTO Money Drive! Our goal this year is $20,000. We are halfway there with only a few days left. The funds from this will go to various projects that the PTO sponsors including buddy benches, replacing wood chips with rubber for the playgrounds and many more activities and supplies for our 1,000+ students here at GWA.

New envelopes will be sent home today with students. The last day to donate is this Friday, September 28th so don't wait! If you would like to donate online please use this link: https://www.gofundme.com/GWAMoneyDrive2018.

The PTO Money Drive begins tomorrow, September 14th so look for envelopes and the Money Drive flyer to come home. Our goal is $20,000, and if we meet our goal, we get a school-wide free dress day. It's very important to completely fill out the front of the envelope before returning it to your child's teacher. If your child's name and teacher are not on the envelope, your child will not get credit for your contribution. Thank you for your support!

We still have the following spots to fill, so please contact us if you or someone you know is interested or has questions:

-Booth Coordinators

We also still have space for vendors who are interested in indoor or outdoor booths. Contact us as soon as possible to reserve a space. If you are interested in being a sponsor, we'd love to speak with you. Thank you!

Suzanne Szabo
fallcarnival@gwacademy.org

Amie Carroll

post_text:
SPED PARAPROFESSIONAL (Part Time)
GWA is looking for a Part Time SPED paraprofessional to provide safety and support for children with special needs. Applicants should enjoy working with children, be patient, and good with taking direction. Some physical requirements required. This position is for a maximum of 18 hours per week. Mon-Thurs 12:00 – 3:00 pm and Fridays 8:00 am -1:00 pm. Associates Degree is required. Will train the right person. Compensation is $13.39 per hour. All employees are required to pass a BCI background check at their own expense. Applications are available on our website at http://www.gwacademy.org . Please send resume and application to hr@gwacademy.org

LUNCH AIDE (PART TIME 18 HOURS PER WEEK)
George Washington Academy is currently looking to hire a lunchroom aide to assist with student supervision during lunch, recess, and general maintenance. Will need to have physical strength (carry bulky objects of up to 50 pounds with or without assistance), and the agility to pull, push, squat, twist, turn and lift. This includes both inside and outside responsibilities. Pay is $10.71 per hour for a total of 18 hours per week 10:30 am – 2:00 pm Monday - Friday. All employees are required to pass a BCI background check at their own expense. Applications are available on our website at www.gwacademy.org. Please send resume and application to hr@gwacademy.org

FOOD SERVICE/KITCHEN STAFF (PART TIME 29 HOURS PER WEEK)
George Washington Academy is currently looking to hire a Food Service/ Kitchen aide to work with our Kitchen Staff helping with cooking and food preparation and the ability to work with and around students, but not supervise students. Must be willing to work in a fast paced environment and able to multitask. Will need to have physical strength (carry bulky objects of up to 50 pounds with or without assistance), and the agility to pull, push, squat, twist, turn and lift. Prefer someone with basic knowledge of cooking procedures, but not required. This is a part time position Monday – Friday approx. 29 hours per week. Will be required to get a Food Handlers Permit. Pay is $10.71 per hour. All employees are required to pass a BCI Background check at their own expense. Applications are available on our website at http://www.gwacademy.org. Send resume and application to hr@gwacademy.org.

This position will be responsible for providing keyboarding instruction to K-2 grade students for the 2018-19 school year for a maximum of 24 hours per week. post_text:
FOOD SERVICE/POINT OF SALES (PART TIME 15-18 hours per week)

George Washington Academy is currently looking to hire a food service/point of sales cashier for the rest of the 2017-18 school year to work with our Kitchen Staff helping with food preparation and the ability to work with and around students as a point of sales cashier. Must be willing to work in a fast paced environment and able to multitask. Prefer someone with basic knowledge of food preparation and cashier but not required. Will sweep/mop/clean and sanitize work areas and help assist with kitchen areas. This is a part time position Monday – Friday 10:30 am – 1:30 pm. Will be required to get a Food Handlers Permit. Pay is $10.71 per hour. All employees are required to pass a BCI Background check at their own expense. Applications are available on our website at www.gwacademy.org. Send resume and application to hr@gwacademy.org

GWA Student Amelia Woolley will perform at Dixie’s Got Talent Finals Tonight! Go Amelia! 😊
shared_text:
Dixie's Got Talent
January 13, 2018 at 2:04 AM ·

Second day of getting to know our finalists!

First we have Zac Greenwell:
•What do you love about Dixie State University?
“I love how personable Dixie State is. The teachers here really care about every student and I think that’s something very special.”
-
Second we have Amelia Woolley:
•Do you have a role model in your field of arts?
“My teachers Jaime Waters and Bené Arnold are my role models because they grew my love for dance. Thank you!”
-
Thirdly we have Haven Sunderlund:
•Why did you decide to first audition for Dixies Got Talent?
“The feeling and excitement of singing in front of a ton of people gives me such a rush!”
#dixiestate #dixietraditions #thedixielife

Instructional Assistant: Mathematics (24 hours per week)
George Washington Academy is looking for an Instructional Assistant for our middle school students (grades 6th-8th) in the Math Lab for a maximum of 24 hours per week Mon-Thurs. 10:00 am – 3:00 pm and possibly Fridays 8:00 am – 12:00 pm. The assistant needs to be very comfortable with math and able to assist students with questions up to secondary math level 1 (9th grade math). Must be comfortable overseeing a group of middle school students. No actual math instruction required, just the ability to assist math teachers and students. They will serve in a position for which a teacher or another professional has ultimate responsibility for the design and implementation of educational services. An approved BCI background check is required and paid for by the employee. Compensation is $10.71 per hour. Applications are available on our website at gwacademy.org. Email application and resume to hr@gwacademy.org

Do you have experience with spray painting and want an easy at-home project to earn a couple of volunteer hours?

We have 25 wood blocks for the donor wall that need to be sprayed with polyurethane, on the fronts and sides. Blocks range in size from 2 square inches to 4 square inches. We prefer 2 coats with a light sanding in between coats.

Please contact 435-215-6061 if you are interested. Blocks should be available to you sometime next week.

Thank you for helping us make our art program amazing for your children! Your help makes a huge difference!

Facility Support Staff (Part time 29 hours per week)

George Washington Academy is currently looking to hire facility support staff for the 2017-18 school year to assist with cleaning and general maintenance, student supervision during lunch, recess, and afternoon carpool. This includes both inside and outside responsibilities. This is a part time position Monday – Thursday (10:30 am-4:00pm) and Friday (10:30 am -2:30 pm). Pay is $10.71 per hour. All employees are required to pass a BCI Background check at their own expense. Applications are available on our website. Send resume and application to hr@gwacademy.org

post_text:
It is time again for the Carnival Cake Decorating Contest and Cake Walk! Submissions must be turned in on Friday, 10/20 by 9 AM in the school gym on the stage. For the contest, we have fabulous prizes for 1st, 2nd, and 3rd place in each category; categories are K-3rd grade, 4th-8th grade, and adults. 1st place winner in each category will be auctioned in the live auction at 2:00 PM on Sat. at the carnival. Winners will be announced at that time. All other cakes will automatically be donated to the cake walk.

We need as many cakes as possible for the cake walk! They don't have to be beautifully decorated, just have them taste yummy!

If you have any questions about the cake walk or decorating contest, please contact Kaile Calder at 801-971-7688. We also need a few volunteers from 7:30-9:30 AM on Friday to help receive and arrange the cakes. Please contact Kaile if you can help!
